The paper discusses the detection and removal of boilerplate content from webpages, specifically focusing on the extraction of relevant images. This involves leveraging a headless browser solution to obtain rendering information for images. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-categories.
